Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Crewe 305 occupies a prominent position on Crewe Commercial Park, a significant new logistics development offering easy access to junction 16 of the M6, as well as a readily available workforce. The West Coast Mainline runs alongside the site as it approaches Crewe station. It is proposed that Crewe will become a hub for HS2, transforming connectivity for passengers and freight services in the region.
Radar comprises 5 manufacturing/distribution (B1/B2/B8 use) units with sizes from 17,924 sq ft up to 59,463 sq ft on an overall site of 28.97 acres.

Ergo Park Middlewich comprises of three brand new speculatively built warehouses available from Q1 2022. Middlewich is strategically located within 2 miles of J18 of the M6 Motorway providing links to Manchester (27 miles), Liverpool (37 miles) and Birmingham (60 miles). Local occupiers include Swizzels, B&M, Wincanton and Optima Logistics. The area benefits from amenities including, a Travel Lodge, Starbucks and Petrol Station.

The unit is located on the corner of First Avenue and Third Avenue on Poynton Industrial Estate with immediate access from A523 London Road. This in turn leads to the A6 Stockport Road offering easy access to Stockport town centre and Manchester beyond. Close to the site will be the A523 Poynton Bypass; a £50m highways investment which is under construction and when completed in 2021, will link to the A555 Manchester Airport Relief Road. This will allow swift access to the Airport, M60 and wider region as well as swifter access to Stockport and the A6.
